main event: A radar track recorded an unusually large blip interpreted as a UFO on 16 Feb 1961.
interesting points: The radar blip was noted as abnormally large compared to regular night reflections., Estimated speed of the object was 1200 mph., The elevation angle changed from 270 to 0 degrees before it disappeared., The report classifies the data as insufficient for clear evaluation., Multiple personnel evaluated the report but found it lacking pertinent information.
witness description: No visual sighting made, based solely on radar data.
